quran[8]{c,v,t}:
  8,62,"But if they seek to betray thee, God will be all-sufficient for thee. He it is who hath strengthened thee with His help, and with the faithful"
  8,63,"and hath made their hearts one. Hadst thou spent all the riches of the earth, thou couldst not have united their hearts; but God hath united them, for He is Mighty, Wise"
  8,64,"O prophet! God, and such of the faithful as follow thee, will be all-sufficient for thee"
  8,65,"O prophet! stir up the faithful to the fight. Twenty of you who stand firm shall vanquish two hundred: and if there be a hundred of you they shall vanquish a thousand of the infidels, for they are a people devoid of understanding"
  8,66,"Now hath God made your work easy, for he knoweth how weak ye are. If there be an hundred of you who endure resolutely, they shall vanquish two hundred; and if there be a thousand of you, they shall vanquish two thousand by God's permission; for God is with those who are resolute to endure"
  8,67,"No prophet hath been enabled to take captives until he had made great slaughter in the earth. Ye desire the passing fruitions of this world, but God desireth the next life for you. And God is Mighty, Wise"
  8,68,"Had there not been a previous ordinance from God, a severe chastisement had befallen you, for the ransom which ye took"
  8,69,"Eat therefore of the spoils ye have taken what is lawful and good; and fear God: God is Gracious, Merciful"